&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an experienced administration manager/officer who has experience of:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;supporting a senior management team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;working flexibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;developing and managing teams through good interpersonal skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;data collation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;organising events&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;If yes, we want to hear from you!&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The GPCP has successfully won service contracts for Health Visiting, Family Nurse Partnership and Scholl Health. We are now creating an integrated 0-19 services with a central administration Hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and enthusiastic administration officer to lead and manage our newly created 0-19 services administration team and manage 6 administration officers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will have previous experience of establishing and maintaining business support systems and processes, managing staff and supporting senior managers. It is essential that the successful candidate has a high level of IT proficiency and experienced in operating Word 365 applications and other IT software applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on Wednesday 18th November 12 noon onwards via Teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
